---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SpecSection from "../components/SpecSection.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="TermCoder — install"
  description="Install TermCoder from npm on Linux, macOS, or Windows, or download the desktop app. One command, no account, no API key."
  active="install.html"
>
  <SpecSection gutter="//">
    <div class="t full">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> INSTALL</div>
      <h2>One command, every platform.</h2>
      <p>No accounts, no API keys, no telemetry. The CLI installs from npm and runs the same on Linux,
        macOS, and Windows. Prefer a window? <a class="link" href="download.html">Download the app</a> —
        Node is bundled, nothing else to set up.</p>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="01">
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">01</span><span class="lbl">INSTALL FROM NPM</span></div>
      <h2>One command.</h2>
      <p>Needs Node.js 18 or newer. No Node? Grab the desktop app instead — it bundles its own.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="cmd-2"><span class="in">$</span><code>npm install -g @termcoder/tui</code></div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="02" rev>
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">02</span><span class="lbl">RUN IT</span></div>
      <h2>Type term anywhere.</h2>
      <p>Open a terminal in any project folder and start. Two commands install — <code>term</code> and
        <code>termcoder</code> — they do the same thing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip"><div class="sbar"><span>~/my-project</span></div><pre><span class="in">$</span> term
<span class="out">&#9679;</span> termcoderfree/auto  <span class="c">free · no key</span>
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> _</pre></div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="03">
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">03</span><span class="lbl">TRUST THE FOLDER</span></div>
      <h2>Once per folder.</h2>
      <p>On first open, TermCoder asks whether you trust the current folder before it reads or runs
        anything in it. Answer once; it remembers per folder.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip"><div class="sbar"><span>trust</span></div><pre>Trust the files in this folder?
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> yes, this is my project
  no, exit</pre></div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="04" rev>
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">04</span><span class="lbl">START, OR CONNECT A MODEL</span></div>
      <h2>Nothing required.</h2>
      <p>It runs on a free, keyless model out of the box. Want faster, stronger answers? Connect one —
        all free options included:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip"><div class="sbar"><span>graduate when you want</span></div><pre><span class="in">&#10095;</span> /upgrade        <span class="c"># free Gemini key, 2 steps</span>
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> /login-claude   <span class="c"># Claude Pro/Max (experimental)</span>
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> /login-chatgpt  <span class="c"># ChatGPT Plus/Pro (experimental)</span>
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> /key google &lt;key&gt;  <span class="c"># or paste one</span></pre></div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="05">
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">05</span><span class="lbl">ASK YOUR FIRST TASK</span></div>
      <h2>Plain language.</h2>
      <p>Describe what you want. It reads the code, proposes edits, and runs commands — asking before
        anything that changes your machine.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip"><div class="sbar"><span>~/my-project</span></div><pre><span class="in">&#10095;</span> add input validation to the signup form,
  then run the tests
<span class="out">&#10003;</span> read signup.ts
<span class="out">&#10003;</span> edit signup.ts
<span class="out">&#10003;</span> npm test  <span class="c">&#8594;</span> <span class="out">passing</span></pre></div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="—">
    <div class="t full">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> OR SKIP NODE</div>
      <h2>Grab the desktop app.</h2>
      <p>Windows, macOS, and Linux installers with Node bundled — nothing to configure.</p>
      <div class="row-2">
        <a class="btn-2 go" href="download.html">Download</a>
        <a class="btn-2" href="docs.html">Read the docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>
</Layout>
